OL,3,CSignal jammers and oath swearing: How
OL,4,Cthe secrecy of the Conclave is enforced
OL,6,FThis time, 120 cardinals in red robes
OL,7,Fwill be sealed inside the Sistine
OL,8,FChapel in Rome, beneath Michelangelo's
OL,9,Ffamous frescoes, for a historic vote.
OL,11,FThe secrecy is meant to ensure their
OL,12,Fdecision is guided by faith, not
OL,13,Foutside influence.
OL,15,FBut how will the Vatican keep the vote
OL,16,Fsecret, as it could take days for a
OL,17,Fnew pope to be chosen?
OL,19,FCommunication signals cut ahead of vote
